gomodel:SYNGO_4824  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1: Dendritic Protrusions Are Significantly Longer in KCC2 (SLC12A5) -/- than in WT Neurons\n\nFigure 2: Reduced Number of Functional Synapses in Dendrites of KCC2 (SLC12A5) -/- Neurons\n\nFigure 5: Transfecting cultured WT neurons with a construct containing the KCC2-CTD only (aa 637-1116) induced long filopodia-like dendritic protrusions. \"These results indicate that the KCC2-CTD mutant has a dominant-negative effect that leads to the disruption of intracellular interactions that are necessary for normal dendritic spine morphogenesis.\". Experimental description: M&M: \"Primary cultures of hippocampal neurons were prepared as previously described10 with some modifications of the protocol. Briefly, hippocampi were dissected from embryonic day 18 or 19 Sprague-Dawley rats of either sex.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2022-09-02" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4824" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

